  "risk_regime": {
    "stance": "risk_on",
    "conviction": 70,
    "rationale": "8 of 10 members are explicitly risk_on (convictions 62\u201382, mean ~75), all on the same footing: structural, long-horizon, builder-oriented bullishness \u2014 'still early innings', product-cycle over financial-cycle, building through the bear market. The 2 remaining members (Thaler, Roughgarden) are no_view by design \u2014 research partners who refuse market/price calls \u2014 so they abstain rather than oppose. Consensus conviction is set at 70, below the risk-on members' mean, to reflect (a) those two abstentions and (b) that this is a structural building posture, not a tactical price/timing call. The bullishness is explicitly paired with near-term defensiveness on US regulation and a desire to clean up CeFi/'casino' excess \u2014 long-term offensive, short-term guarded.",
    "provenance": "grounded"
  },
  "notes": "Consensus weighted by genuine cross-member breadth \u00d7 conviction, with high-dispersion items neutralized. IMPORTANT caveat on the dispersion table: 'coverage' counts item ENTRIES, not distinct members \u2014 e.g. zk's coverage of 7 spans 5 members (Thaler logged 3 ZK entries), and snark-security's coverage of 4 is entirely Thaler, so it was downgraded to a single-member specialist concern despite its 80 mean conviction. Strongest, broadest convictions: ZK/privacy, L2 scaling, decentralization (ideological core), AI\u00d7crypto (freshest rising theme), and ETH as the consensus fundamentals token. Items deliberately treated as NEUTRAL / no house view due to genuine internal splits (stance dispersion \u22481.0, mean sign 0): governance-dao (mean sign +0.33, members range bullish-to-skeptical), dao-legal-entities (Jennings bullish on legal wrappers / bearish on the liability they fix), nft-mint-mechanism-design (Kominers bullish on good auction design / bearish on prevailing practice), and lvr-amm-loss (Roughgarden's two-sided LP-loss research) \u2014 these are excluded from both excited and concerned lists rather than forced into a stance. crypto-policy-regulation is the most consequential genuine split (US-pessimist vs. UK-optimist) and is carried as a moderated concern, not a high-conviction one. The corpus is dominated by structural/thesis views from investors, engineers, lawyers, and academics rather than traders, so nearly all token entries are infrastructure/fundamentals/legal-test-case views, NOT directional price calls; single-member token views (BTC, DAI, LDO, LUNA, FTT, XRP \u2014 almost all Jennings or Matsuoka) were faded hard for lack of coverage. No items were invented; member item names reused verbatim."
}